<li>Group: group 2 (alkaline earth metals)</li>
<li>Block: s-block</li>
<li>Period: period 3</li>
<li>Element category: alkaline earth metal</li>
<li>Electron configuration: 3s2</li>
<li>Per shell: 2, 8, 2</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Physical properties</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Phase: solid</li>
<li>Melting point: 923 K ​(650 °C, ​1202 °F)</li>
<li>Boiling point: 1363 K ​(1091 °C, ​1994 °F)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>History</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Discovery: Joseph Black (1755)</li>
<li>Naming: after Magnesia, Greece</li>
<li>First isolation: Humphry Davy (1808)</li>
</ul>
